For {= molecule =}+ active drug molecules, name {= scientist =}+ scientists who appear as authors on each molecule's discovery / disclosure / synthesis paper, and supply that paper as the source (i.e. {= url =}+ URL). Each molecule must be a real active molecule.

Requirements:
- The cited URL must be a discovery / disclosure / synthesis paper for the claimed molecule — a paper presenting the molecule's first publication, disclosure, or synthesis as its subject. Class-survey review articles (covering many compounds), efficacy-focused clinical trial reports, and papers about a downstream application are NOT discovery papers. Discovery papers may title the molecule by its development code rather than the later API name.
- The scientist must appear in the author list of the cited paper (any byline position counts). PubMed-style "Lastname AB" initial bylines are equivalent to the full "Alice B. Lastname" when surname and initials match unambiguously.
- The molecule must be a primary subject of the paper (named in title and/or abstract), not merely mentioned in passing. The development-code form counts when the cited paper consistently uses it.
